<paragraph id="8BB436EEFFCD0863450EF8BF63DCFD85" blockId="34.[264,1323,1836,1902]" lastBlockId="35.[264,1323,284,590]" lastPageId="35" lastPageNumber="36" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFCD0862450EF8BF65EAF88D" authority="Smith, 1911" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1911" box="[264,668,1836,1862]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Perigonica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fermata">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFCD0862450EF8BF6683F88E" box="[264,501,1836,1861]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Perigonica fermata</emphasis>
Smith, 
<number id="3DC324C9FFCD08624665F8BF65EAF88D" box="[611,668,1836,1862]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" value="1911.0">1911</number>
</taxonomicName>
was described from San Diego, California; it was diagnosed as a reddish species very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFCD0862472CF8C764F0F8A6" box="[810,902,1876,1901]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Perigonica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tertia">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFCD0862472CF8C764F0F8A6" box="[810,902,1876,1901]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">P. tertia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the 
<typeStatus id="54B0884CFFCD0862403DF8C763D0F8A5" box="[1083,1190,1876,1902]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFCD086240C8F8C76251F8A6" box="[1230,1319,1876,1901]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">P. t e r t i a</emphasis>
(
<collectionCode id="ED1AAE2BFFCC08634516FE8F661EFEFD" LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" box="[272,360,284,310]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">USNM</collectionCode>
) and all specimens from southern California that I have dissected, including reddish specimens that match the 
<typeStatus id="54B0884CFFCC086346A1FED76593FE95" box="[679,741,324,350]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">types</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFCC08634715FED76418FE96" box="[787,878,324,349]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Perigonica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fermata">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFCC08634715FED76418FE96" box="[787,878,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">fermata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, are identical in genital morphology (
<figureCitation id="13302A6BFFCC08634517FEFF661DFE4D" box="[273,363,364,390]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 63" captionStartId="45.[264,362,1527,1551]" captionTargetBox="[292,1293,316,1500]" captionTargetId="figure@45.[292,1294,316,1504]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 63. Male genitalia of the new described species and related species: 40, Protoperigea calientensis (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 41, Aseptis fanatica (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 42, Aseptis ethnica. 43, Aseptis ferruginea. 44, Aseptis torreyana (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 45, Aseptis serrula. 46, Apamea robertsoni (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 47, Apamea digitula (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 48, Apamea sordens. 49, Photedes sofiae. 50, Mammifrontia sarae (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 51, Mammifrontia rileyi (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 52, Benjaminola colorada (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 53, Perigonica tertia. 54, Perigonica fulminans. 55, Perigonica angulata. 56, Anarta fusculenta (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 57, Anarta crotchi (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 58, Anarta oaklandiae. 59, Lasionycta sala (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 60, Trichocerapoda harbisoni (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 61, Trichocerapoda comstocki. 62, Trichocerapoda oceanis (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 63. Hexorthodes nipana." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273512/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC324C9FFCC0863454CFEFF661DFE4D" box="[330,363,364,390]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="53.0">53</number>
</figureCitation>
). While the 
<typeStatus id="54B0884CFFCC08634607FEFF6549FE4D" box="[513,575,364,390]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">types</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFCC0863466AFEFF65B1FE4E" box="[620,711,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">P. t e r t i a</emphasis>
are pale specimens, the species shows remarkable variation in southern California, with the ground color ranging from pale yellowish gray to pinkish, rusty red, brown, and dark grayish brown. The amount of dark dusting and maculation also varies considerably. However, based on male genitalia these color forms appear to represent a single species. In contrast, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFCC08634749FD9F639CFDED" authority="Smith, 1888" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1888" box="[847,1258,524,550]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Perigonica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulminans">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFCC08634749FD9F6339FDEE" box="[847,1103,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Perigonica fulminans</emphasis>
Smith, 
<number id="3DC324C9FFCC086340A9FD9F639CFDED" box="[1199,1258,524,550]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="1888.0">1888</number>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13302A6BFFCC086340FDFD9F6651FD85" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 63" captionStartId="45.[264,362,1527,1551]" captionTargetBox="[292,1293,316,1500]" captionTargetId="figure@45.[292,1294,316,1504]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 63. Male genitalia of the new described species and related species: 40, Protoperigea calientensis (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 41, Aseptis fanatica (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 42, Aseptis ethnica. 43, Aseptis ferruginea. 44, Aseptis torreyana (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 45, Aseptis serrula. 46, Apamea robertsoni (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 47, Apamea digitula (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 48, Apamea sordens. 49, Photedes sofiae. 50, Mammifrontia sarae (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 51, Mammifrontia rileyi (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 52, Benjaminola colorada (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 53, Perigonica tertia. 54, Perigonica fulminans. 55, Perigonica angulata. 56, Anarta fusculenta (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 57, Anarta crotchi (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 58, Anarta oaklandiae. 59, Lasionycta sala (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 60, Trichocerapoda harbisoni (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 61, Trichocerapoda comstocki. 62, Trichocerapoda oceanis (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 63. Hexorthodes nipana." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273512/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC324C9FFCC0863450EFDA76651FD85" box="[264,295,564,590]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="54.0">54</number>
</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFCC0863456EFDA765F3FD85" authority="Smith, 1890" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1890" box="[360,645,564,590]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Perigonica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angulata">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFCC0863456EFDA7669BFD86" box="[360,493,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">P. angulata</emphasis>
Smith, 
<number id="3DC324C9FFCC0863464CFDA765F3FD85" box="[586,645,564,590]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="1890.0">1890</number>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13302A6BFFCC08634692FDA7659FFD85" box="[660,745,564,590]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 63" captionStartId="45.[264,362,1527,1551]" captionTargetBox="[292,1293,316,1500]" captionTargetId="figure@45.[292,1294,316,1504]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 63. Male genitalia of the new described species and related species: 40, Protoperigea calientensis (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 41, Aseptis fanatica (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 42, Aseptis ethnica. 43, Aseptis ferruginea. 44, Aseptis torreyana (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 45, Aseptis serrula. 46, Apamea robertsoni (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 47, Apamea digitula (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 48, Apamea sordens. 49, Photedes sofiae. 50, Mammifrontia sarae (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 51, Mammifrontia rileyi (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 52, Benjaminola colorada (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 53, Perigonica tertia. 54, Perigonica fulminans. 55, Perigonica angulata. 56, Anarta fusculenta (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 57, Anarta crotchi (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 58, Anarta oaklandiae. 59, Lasionycta sala (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 60, Trichocerapoda harbisoni (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 61, Trichocerapoda comstocki. 62, Trichocerapoda oceanis (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 63. Hexorthodes nipana." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273512/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC324C9FFCC086346CDFDA7659FFD85" box="[715,745,564,590]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" value="55.0">55</number>
</figureCitation>
) have distinctive valve morphologies.
</paragraph>
